  <md:abstract>In the 18th and 19th centuries, economists sought to explain what determines the price of a good or service by determining its objective value. In this video Professor Dan Russell of the University of Arizona discusses the labor theory of value, which said that the value of a good or service could be determined by the amount of work needed to produce it.</md:abstract>
